as if it were your own problem.

138
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:04,544
Crying at that. You were one crazy dude.

139
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:07,922
You know,

140
00:09:08,005 --> 00:09:11,676
I was born in a well-to-do family,
but I didn't have a sense of vocation.

141
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:14,929
I just asked my parents to send me to
the US so that I could go to law school.

142
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:18,724
All I did there was have a good time,
and the first thing I saw when I got back

143
00:09:20,059 --> 00:09:21,852
was pretty cool.

144
00:09:21,936 --> 00:09:23,396
The power you had

145
00:09:23,813 --> 00:09:28,818
was like a special limited edition.

146
00:09:28,901 --> 00:09:32,238
Something you couldn't get
with money or connections.

147
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:33,948
So,

148
00:09:34,031 --> 00:09:36,701
since I was going to start my own firm
once I passed the bar,

149
00:09:36,784 --> 00:09:37,868
I believed you could

150
00:09:37,952 --> 00:09:40,204
be the conscience of the firm.

151
00:09:41,497 --> 00:09:42,540
That's why

152
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:46,586
I hired you myself, so why would I
regret it? I care about you.

153
00:09:49,005 --> 00:09:52,216
But you weren't happy here,
so it bothered me

154
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,884
that I might be the cause.

155
00:09:54,844 --> 00:09:57,680
You're the one who helped me
stick through it this far.

156
00:09:59,098 --> 00:10:00,057
Thank you.

157
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:03,436
That's true.

158
00:10:06,814 --> 00:10:08,774
An article is coming out tomorrow
about my father.

159
00:10:08,858 --> 00:10:10,109
Along with my name.

160
00:10:11,569 --> 00:10:12,820
Once it comes out,

161
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:15,406
the Ye Chung-sik case
will come under scrutiny.

162
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:19,577
It'll seem like I betrayed my client
to cover for my father.

163
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,371
The firm will come under fire too.

164
00:10:28,836 --> 00:10:31,547
I told you in advance this time,
so I hope you forgive me.

165
00:10:31,631 --> 00:10:33,466
RESIGNATION LETTER

166
00:10:33,549 --> 00:10:35,343
What's the truth?

167
00:10:38,012 --> 00:10:40,473
Did you turn Ye Chung-sik in
knowing about your father?

168
00:10:40,556 --> 00:10:41,974
Is that the truth?

169
00:10:42,058 --> 00:10:43,976
I'm also a lawyer who seeks the truth.

170
00:10:44,060 --> 00:10:46,145
I have a duty to defend

171
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:49,148
the truth too. It's not just you.

172
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:54,403
I can't turn away from my conscience
just to avoid rumors and fake newsâ€¦

173
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:55,446
Gyu.

174
00:10:55,529 --> 00:10:57,114
